      "note_no": "3648",
      "note": "Junub: sides, on which men sleep and turn in their sleep: I have translated this \"limbs\" for shortness. Holy men and women \"breathless with adoration\" shun soft, comfortable beds, and luxurious sleep. Their limbs are better exercised in offices of devotion and prayer, especially by night. Commentators specially refer this to Prayers called Tahajjud, which are offered after midnight in the small hours of the morning, in twelve Rak'as."
